<div id="review_2344945017" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2344945017" />
    <a title="Craig" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8691746-craig"><img alt="Craig" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2344945017?book_show_action=true">Mar 30, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Craig" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Craig" href="/user/show/8691746-craig">Craig</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2344945017" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16260715779750728417">It&apos;s easy to get a sense of vertigo trying to correlate all of the names of the people and places described in this book, but this is both a good introduction for someone new to the topic of the Mongols as well as a fine supplement for those who are not. It provides a wide sweep of the huge Mongol Empire on all levels, from the gear that an individual Mongol horseman would take on campaign, to Mongol tactics, leadership profiles and cultural aberrations and impacts. It also dispels many of the p</span>
  <span id="freeText16260715779750728417" style="display:none">It's easy to get a sense of vertigo trying to correlate all of the names of the people and places described in this book, but this is both a good introduction for someone new to the topic of the Mongols as well as a fine supplement for those who are not. It provides a wide sweep of the huge Mongol Empire on all levels, from the gear that an individual Mongol horseman would take on campaign, to Mongol tactics, leadership profiles and cultural aberrations and impacts. It also dispels many of the preconceptions of the world many people have today and I often suggest this book to those who think brutal, invasive imperialism, genocide, induced mass slavery and a contempt for the cultures of others is only a European practice and characteristic.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16260715779750728417" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
