<div id="review_133741292" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/133741292" />
    <a title="Suzanne Moore" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2127114-suzanne-moore"><img alt="Suzanne Moore" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1263773818p2/2127114.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/133741292?book_show_action=true">Dec 05, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzanne Moore" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzanne Moore" href="/user/show/2127114-suzanne-moore">Suzanne Moore</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2127114-suzanne-moore?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2127114-suzanne-moore?shelf=winter-challenge-picks">winter-challenge-picks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2127114-suzanne-moore?shelf=world-history">world-history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer133741292" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2128430113210940911">The history of Genghis Khan and his offspring was long and complicated to me. More than likely it was the difficulty in pronouncing names and places, along with visualizing where all the places lie in relation to each other that made processing all the details difficult. One thing I learned was the devastation left in the wake of these warrior Mongols, on horseback, was horrific. The Mongol empire was built on the plunder and massacre of many civilians. The territories gained throughout the conq</span>
  <span id="freeText2128430113210940911" style="display:none">The history of Genghis Khan and his offspring was long and complicated to me. More than likely it was the difficulty in pronouncing names and places, along with visualizing where all the places lie in relation to each other that made processing all the details difficult. One thing I learned was the devastation left in the wake of these warrior Mongols, on horseback, was horrific. The Mongol empire was built on the plunder and massacre of many civilians. The territories gained throughout the conquest were said to cover most of Central Asia and China. Chambers documents that Khan solicited advice from Buddhist monks, the Catholic Church, Muslims, and Christian missionaries, seeking alliances with Kings and European royalty. <br /><br /> New techniques and technologies were introduced and attributed to the successful warfare strategies. I thought it was very clever that silk clothes were worn under the heavier battle attire. The silk cloth was so tightly woven that it couldn’t be penetrated by even the sharpest arrow point. Although arrows would pierce outer garments, the silk would only tear, encasing the arrowheads as they entered the flesh. Before protective silk, arrows had to be pushed through the body, because pulling them out usually made the entry wound bigger and more difficult to heal. But with silk, a careful pull on the fabric allowed arrows to be worked out leaving a smaller, cleaner wound. <br /> <br />Battles in the Middle East, Iran, Turkey, Russia, and Persia are among the highlights of the conquests. Although Khan was unfavorably credited for destroying large populations in genocidal warfare, he is remembered for his great military leadership. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2128430113210940911" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


